WEEK 4 ANSWERS
4. The Power of Storytelling in Literature:
Storytelling is a fundamental aspect of human culture, connecting us across time and space. In literature, stories serve as windows into diverse worlds, emotions, and experiences. Through characters, settings, and plotlines, authors convey universal truths and provoke thought and empathy. The interpretation of literature is deeply personal, and the impact of a well-crafted story can be profound, sparking discussions, shaping identities, and inspiring change.
